 (speed of light), "slowing down" through space is just rotating the vector so more of its speed is directed through time (or vice versa).
E. Schrödinger’s Equation
The wave equation that governs quantum mechanics is reinterpreted here as the "continuous phase evolution" of the spinning arrows.
4. Summary
The "Architect" presents a comprehensive model where the universe is a Holographic Projection from a non-local singularity.
The singularity is a timeless ocean of spinning information. When density gets too high, it creates black holes (memory nodes) that project data onto an event horizon. This projection happens in "flashes" (Planck time), creating the illusion of time and motion.
The fundamental unit is the Quantum State Vector (QSV). Its angle determines everything: how fast it moves, how likely it is to exist, and how it interacts with gravity. The laws of physics—Einstein’s gravity, Feynman’s paths, and Schrödinger’s waves—are all just different ways of describing the rotation of these light arrows. Consciousness is the biological process of decoding these arrows back into experience.